The paper discusses the use of machine learning for automated monitoring of croplands using remote sensing data. This involves image processing and classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the challenges and opportunities for machine learning in this domain, which suggests that it belongs to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of data from earth observing satellites suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the proposed approaches for crop monitoring, which may involve computational engineering (cs.CE) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
